\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {section}{\numberline {5.1}High-level Architecture}{13}{section.5.1}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces GiTrip high-level architecture. The browser communicates with the Express server over HTTP/JSON. \textit  {UI Routes} render pages while \textit  {API Routes} delegate to the \textit  {Planner}, \textit  {Merge}, \textit  {Routing}, and \textit  {Geo Search} modules. \textit  {Quick Route} delegates to \textit  {Routing}, which in turn calls ORS for non-transit modes and Google Directions for transit legs. The \textit  {Planner} consults the \textit  {Opening Hours Parser}, a local utility that validates time intervals against OSM opening-hours strings supplied by Nominatim via \textit  {Geo Search}. Authentication middleware enforces session management, rate-limiting, and Content Security Policy headers across all routes. Server route handlers fetch weather forecasts from Open-Meteo and travel alerts from GNews. All persistent state is stored in a SQLite database.}}{14}{figure.caption.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{5.1}{14}{GiTrip high-level architecture. The browser communicates with the Express server over HTTP/JSON. \textit {UI Routes} render pages while \textit {API Routes} delegate to the \textit {Planner}, \textit {Merge}, \textit {Routing}, and \textit {Geo Search} modules. \textit {Quick Route} delegates to \textit {Routing}, which in turn calls ORS for non-transit modes and Google Directions for transit legs. The \textit {Planner} consults the \textit {Opening Hours Parser}, a local utility that validates time intervals against OSM opening-hours strings supplied by Nominatim via \textit {Geo Search}. Authentication middleware enforces session management, rate-limiting, and Content Security Policy headers across all routes. Server route handlers fetch weather forecasts from Open-Meteo and travel alerts from GNews. All persistent state is stored in a SQLite database}{figure.caption.8}{}}
