\newlabel{fig:uml_class}{{5.3}{17}{UML class diagram for GiTrip's server-side modules. Each module is shown with public (\texttt {+}) and private (\texttt {-}) operations. Dashed open arrows denote $\langle \!\langle $use$\rangle \!\rangle $ dependencies; the filled diamond denotes composition (Server owns TTLCache instances). \texttt {TTLCache} is a formal JavaScript class; all other boxes are CommonJS modules}{figure.caption.10}{}}
