\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.4}{\ignorespaces Three-way merge decision flowchart. The engine iterates all file keys, recording conflicts or taking the changed side, then checks plan divergence. If both sides changed the plan identically, either is taken. If both changed the plan structure and their stop-key Jaccard similarity is below~0.4, a whole-plan conflict is raised. Otherwise, per-stop merging chains through deletion, time, and field checks. The result is stabilised by deterministic ordering before output.}}{19}{figure.caption.11}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:merge_flow}{{5.4}{19}{Three-way merge decision flowchart. The engine iterates all file keys, recording conflicts or taking the changed side, then checks plan divergence. If both sides changed the plan identically, either is taken. If both changed the plan structure and their stop-key Jaccard similarity is below~0.4, a whole-plan conflict is raised. Otherwise, per-stop merging chains through deletion, time, and field checks. The result is stabilised by deterministic ordering before output}{figure.caption.11}{}}
